oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Williams. Elbert & Mary Williams home, Maryville Pike, ca. 1875
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Elbert & Mary Williams home, Maryville Pike, ca. 1875. In 1991, known as the Williams - Henson home. In front of house: cattle with cart and young African American boy, man standing near wagon, couple seated in chairs, and dog in chair.
